        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 5:22PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Port Clinton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sandusky, Kelleys Island, Sandusky South, and Fairview Lanes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
